$interpreted: Tindoiimu: (I know this road...)
Juan Yun: We should be close now. You know what they say, "You can't go home again", but... not sure how you feel about that...
Tindoiimu: (Nine years...  almost there...  almost there...)
Juan Yun: Princess Tindoiimu?
Tindoiimu: (King... Queen... your daughter has finally returned...)
Juan Yun: .........
Juan Yun: ...*knock knock*... Oh beautiful maiden, where has your mind flown off to? May I come along?
Tindoiimu: ...Lord Juan Yun, what's the matter?
Juan Yun: I've been trying to talk with you this entire journey, but it's like you're in another dimension.
Tindoiimu: I don't want to be misunderstood.
Juan Yun: I only wish to chat. Are you worried about me, from before? You really don't have to be, princess.
Tindoiimu: I heard mythics use spirit energy to harness the power of nature... but you can't? is there something wrong with you?
Juan Yun: I'm fine. Even better now, knowing such a pretty girl cares so much about my health.
Tindoiimu: That's great. Then you should probably head back to the front, with the others.
Juan Yun: Are you upset about something?
Tindoiimu: I wouldn't dare be upset.
Juan Yun: So if you dared, then you would be~ Hah
Juan Yun: For a political hostage, you are simply adorable~
Tindoiimu: What did you say!?
Juan Yun: See, what did I tell you?
Juan Yun: Perhaps, being so close to home, you've relaxed a bit?
Tindoiimu: .........
Juan Yun: ...Yes. This I can understand.
Juan Yun: I also love my home.
Tindoiimu: ...Lord Juan Yun, why did you get so serious all of a sudden...
Juan Yun: Ow, that hurts! The princess thinks I'm never serious...?
Tindoiimu: .........
Juan Yun: .........
Tindoiimu: .........
Tindoiimu: .........
Juan Yun: ...Hey, at least lie and make me feel better...
Juan Yun: Forget it. Can't blame you. I know that I get attached to people, places, things much too easily... people say I'm overly affectionate.
Tindoiimu: (...Keep trying to sweet talk me, buddy...)
Juan Yun: But among them all, my homeland takes top priority.
Juan Yun: So please, believe me that I can understand how you feel.
Juan Yun: The feeling of being far from one's home...
Tindoiimu: .........
Bodyguard: Be careful! They're coming our way!
Juan Yun: ...*huff*...*puff*... Finally drove them off. Where's... everyone else?
Tindoiimu: Don't know. They must have scattered during the chaos.
Tindoiimu: (What happened...? When I was little, there were no wild beasts around here...)
Juan Yun: Ugh... What a pain~
Tindoiimu: Let's go. If we follow this road, there'll be a village up ahead.
Juan Yun: Eh? You are a princess, but you've been to these back roads?
Tindoiimu: ...I am not a lady of the court, if that's what you expect.
Juan Yun: Oh?
Tindoiimu: It'd be meaningless to say any more. Let's go.
Tindoiimu: How did this...
Alliance Trooper: Number 38! You weren't here for role call yesterday! Speak! Where'd you go!?
Scared Insect: I-I-I...
Alliance Trooper: Louder! You sound like a scared little cricket! Don't you insects know how to use your words!?
Scared Insect: I-I-I...
Observing Trooper: Haha, lookie here. So scared he can't even talk~
Alliance Trooper: Screw it. Doesn't want to talk!? Then beat it out of him!
Tindoiimu: No!
Alliance Trooper: Faster! How am I supposed to aim like this!?
Baited Insect: ...O-O-Officer, I'm frightened! I can't do this...
Alliance Trooper: Oh shut up! I'm having a blast. If you can't do it, I might as well shoot you dead, maggot!
Alliance Trooper: My brothers died at your hands and you think I've got no reason for revenge!?
Baited Insect: N-N-N-No... I'll be bait...
Baited Insect: Hey! Got some good food right here!
Tindoiimu: (So they're the ones who brought those beasts here...!?)
Juan Yun: This... this is too much...
Tindoiimu: .........
Panicked Insect: Sir, please. I didn't mean anything by it!
Panicked Insect: I really don't remember where I put it!
Tindoiimu: That's...!
Juan Yun: Ah! Wait for me!
Juan Yun: So your ankle is healed, I see. At least try to act the part...
Alliance Trooper: No passing without I.D. Those are the rules.
Alliance Trooper: If you keep making noise, I'm gonna feed you to the beasts!
Panicking Insect: Please, I'm begging you. If I don't bring this medicine back, my mother is going to die.
Alliance Trooper: Hilarious. What does your mother dying have to do with me?
Alliance Trooper: When my mother died, I didn't see any of you come help.
Alliance Trooper: Hey, get this dumb maggot outta here. Feed it to the beasts!
Tindoiimu: Stop!
Alliance Trooper: Who are you!? Some insect dares get in the way of the Alliance Army? You got a death wish!?
Tindoiimu: Hmph. The Insect Tribe serves the East Alliance, it's true.
Tindoiimu: But a mere pawn who thinks he can act with authority—You both should learn your place!
Alliance Trooper: You crazy... what'd you—
Yu: Well then, is the general allowed to act with authority?
Alliance Trooper: General Yu!
Yu: Seems your skills aren't bad.
Yu: Now report your name and purpose for being here, while you still have the chance!
